567 static void MmwDemo_setSubFramePendingState(MmwDemo_DPC_ObjDet_DynCfg *cfg, uint32_t offset)
568 {
569  switch (offset)
570  {
571  case MMWDEMO_GUIMONSEL_OFFSET:

573  break;
574  case MMWDEMO_CFARCFGRANGE_OFFSET:
575  cfg->isCfarCfgRangePending = 1;
576  break;
577  case MMWDEMO_CFARCFGDOPPLER_OFFSET:
578  cfg->isCfarCfgDopplerPending = 1;
579  break;
580  case MMWDEMO_FOVRANGE_OFFSET:
581  cfg->isFovRangePending = 1;
582  break;
583  case MMWDEMO_FOVDOPPLER_OFFSET:
584  cfg->isFovDopplerPending = 1;
585  break;
586  case MMWDEMO_FOVAOA_OFFSET:
587  cfg->isFovAoaCfgPending = 1;
588  break;
589  case MMWDEMO_MULTIOBJBEAMFORMING_OFFSET:
590  cfg->isMultiObjBeamFormingCfgPending = 1;
591  break;
592  case MMWDEMO_CALIBDCRANGESIG_OFFSET:
593  cfg->isCalibDcRangeSigCfg = 1;
594  break;
595  case MMWDEMO_STATICCLUTTERREMOFVAL_OFFSET:
596  cfg->isStaticClutterRemovalCfgPending = 1;
597  break;
598  case MMWDEMO_ADCBUFCFG_OFFSET:
599  /* do nothing */
600  break;
601  default:
602  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
603  break;
604  }

802 void MmwDemo_CfgUpdate(void *srcPtr, uint32_t offset, uint32_t size, int8_t subFrameNum)
803 {
804  /* if subFrameNum undefined, broadcast to all sub-frames */
805  if(subFrameNum == MMWDEMO_SUBFRAME_NUM_FRAME_LEVEL_CONFIG)
806  {
807  uint8_t indx;
808  for(indx = 0; indx < RL_MAX_SUBFRAMES; indx++)
809  {
810  memcpy((void *)((uint32_t) &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[indx] + offset), srcPtr, size);
811  MmwDemo_setSubFramePendingState(&gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[indx].objDetDynCfg, offset);
812  }
813  }
814  else
815  {
816  /* Apply configuration to specific subframe (or to position zero for the legacy case
817  where there is no advanced frame config) */
818  memcpy((void *)((uint32_t) &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[subFrameNum] + offset), srcPtr, size);
819  MmwDemo_setSubFramePendingState(&gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[subFrameNum].objDetDynCfg, offset);
820  }
821 }

866 static void MmwDemo_transmitProcessedOutput
867 (
868  UART_Handle uartHandle,
869  DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *result,
870  MmwDemo_output_message_stats *timingInfo
871 )
872 {
873  MmwDemo_output_message_header header;
874  MmwDemo_GuiMonSel *pGuiMonSel;
875  MmwDemo_SubFrameCfg *subFrameCfg;
876  uint32_t tlvIdx = 0;
877  uint32_t index;
878  uint32_t numPaddingBytes;
879  uint32_t packetLen;
880  uint8_t padding[MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN];
881  MmwDemo_output_message_tl tl[MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_MAX];
882  int32_t errCode;
883  uint16_t *detMatrix = (uint16_t *)result->detMatrix.data;
884  DPIF_PointCloudCartesian *objOut;
885  cmplx16ImRe_t *azimuthStaticHeatMap;
886  DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo *objOutSideInfo;
887  DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats *stats;
888 
889  /* Get subframe configuration */
890  subFrameCfg = &gMmwMssMCB.subFrameCfg[result->subFrameIdx];
891 
892  /* Get Gui Monitor configuration */
893  pGuiMonSel = &subFrameCfg->guiMonSel;
894 
895  /* Clear message header */
896  memset((void *)&header, 0, sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_header));
897 
898  /******************************************************************
899  Send out data that is enabled, Since processing results are from DSP,
900  address translation is needed for buffer pointers
901  *******************************************************************/
902  {
903  detMatrix = (uint16_t *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)detMatrix,
904  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
905  &errCode);
906  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)detMatrix!= SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
907 
908  objOut = (DPIF_PointCloudCartesian *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)result->objOut,
909  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
910  &errCode);
911  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)objOut != SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
912 
913  objOutSideInfo = (DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)result->objOutSideInfo,
914  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
915  &errCode);
916  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)objOutSideInfo != SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
917 
918  stats = (DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)result->stats,
919  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
920  &errCode);
921  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)stats != SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
922 
923 
924  result->radarCube.data = (void *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t) result->radarCube.data,
925  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
926  &errCode);
927  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t) result->radarCube.data!= SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
928  }
929 
930  /* Header: */
931  header.platform = 0xA1843;
932  header.magicWord[0] = 0x0102;
933  header.magicWord[1] = 0x0304;
934  header.magicWord[2] = 0x0506;
935  header.magicWord[3] = 0x0708;
936  header.numDetectedObj = result->numObjOut;
937  header.version = MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUILD |
938  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_BUGFIX << 8) |
939  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MINOR << 16) |
940  (MMWAVE_SDK_VERSION_MAJOR << 24);
941 
942  packetLen = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_header);
943  if ((pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 1) || (pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 2) &&
944  (result->numObjOut > 0))
945  {
946  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_DETECTED_POINTS;
947  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudCartesian) * result->numObjOut;
948  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
949  tlvIdx++;
950  }
951  /* Side info */
952  if ((pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 1) && (result->numObjOut > 0))
953  {
954  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_DETECTED_POINTS_SIDE_INFO;
955  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo) * result->numObjOut;
956  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
957  tlvIdx++;
958  }
959  if (pGuiMonSel->logMagRange)
960  {
961  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_RANGE_PROFILE;
962  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(uint16_t) * subFrameCfg->numRangeBins;
963  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
964  tlvIdx++;
965  }
966  if (pGuiMonSel->noiseProfile)
967  {
968  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_NOISE_PROFILE;
969  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(uint16_t) * subFrameCfg->numRangeBins;
970  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
971  tlvIdx++;
972  }
973  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeAzimuthHeatMap)
974  {
975  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_AZIMUT_STATIC_HEAT_MAP;
976  tl[tlvIdx].length = result->azimuthStaticHeatMapSize * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
977  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
978  tlvIdx++;
979  }
980  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeDopplerHeatMap)
981  {
982  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_RANGE_DOPPLER_HEAT_MAP;
983  tl[tlvIdx].length = subFrameCfg->numRangeBins * subFrameCfg->numDopplerBins * sizeof(uint16_t);
984  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
985  tlvIdx++;
986  }
987  if (pGuiMonSel->statsInfo)
988  {
989  tl[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_STATS;
990  tl[tlvIdx].length = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_stats);
991  packetLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + tl[tlvIdx].length;
992  tlvIdx++;
993  }
994 
995  header.numTLVs = tlvIdx;
996  /* Round up packet length to multiple of MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN */
997  header.totalPacketLen = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN *
998  ((packetLen + (MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN-1))/MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN);
999  header.timeCpuCycles = Pmu_getCount(0);
1000  header.frameNumber = stats->frameStartIntCounter;
1001  header.subFrameNumber = result->subFrameIdx;
1002 
1003  UART_writePolling (uartHandle,
1004  (uint8_t*)&header,
1005  sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_header));
1006 
1007  tlvIdx = 0;
1008  /* Send detected Objects */
1009  if ((pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 1) || (pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 2) &&
1010  (result->numObjOut > 0))
1011  {
1012  UART_writePolling (uartHandle,
1013  (uint8_t*)&tl[tlvIdx],
1014  sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl));
1015 
1016  /*Send array of objects */
1017  UART_writePolling (uartHandle, (uint8_t*)objOut,
1018  sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudCartesian) * result->numObjOut);
1019  tlvIdx++;
1020  }
1021 
1022  /* Send detected Objects Side Info */
1023  if ((pGuiMonSel->detectedObjects == 1) && (result->numObjOut > 0))
1024  {
1025 
1026  UART_writePolling (uartHandle,
1027  (uint8_t*)&tl[tlvIdx],
1028  sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl));
1029 
1030  UART_writePolling (uartHandle, (uint8_t*)objOutSideInfo,
1031  sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo) * result->numObjOut);
1032  tlvIdx++;
1033  }
1034 
1035  /* Send Range profile */
1036  if (pGuiMonSel->logMagRange)
1037  {
1038  UART_writePolling (uartHandle,
1039  (uint8_t*)&tl[tlvIdx],
1040  sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl));
1041 
1042  for(index = 0; index < subFrameCfg->numRangeBins; index++)
1043  {
1044  UART_writePolling (uartHandle,
1045  (uint8_t*)&detMatrix[index*subFrameCfg->numDopplerBins],
1046  sizeof(uint16_t));
1047  }
1048  tlvIdx++;
1049  }
1050 
1051  /* Send noise profile */
1052  if (pGuiMonSel->noiseProfile)
1053  {
1054  uint32_t maxDopIdx = subFrameCfg->numDopplerBins/2 -1;
1055  UART_writePolling (uartHandle,
1056  (uint8_t*)&tl[tlvIdx],
1057  sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl));
1058 
1059  for(index = 0; index < subFrameCfg->numRangeBins; index++)
1060  {
1061  UART_writePolling (uartHandle,
1062  (uint8_t*)&detMatrix[index*subFrameCfg->numDopplerBins + maxDopIdx],
1063  sizeof(uint16_t));
1064  }
1065  tlvIdx++;
1066  }
1067 
1068  /* Send data for static azimuth heatmap */
1069  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeAzimuthHeatMap)
1070  {
1071  azimuthStaticHeatMap = (cmplx16ImRe_t *) SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)result->azimuthStaticHeatMap,
1072  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_FROM_OTHER_CPU,
1073  &errCode);
1074  DebugP_assert ((uint32_t)azimuthStaticHeatMap!= SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID);
1075 
1076  UART_writePolling (uartHandle,
1077  (uint8_t*)&tl[tlvIdx],
1078  sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl));
1079 
1080  UART_writePolling (uartHandle,
1081  (uint8_t *)azimuthStaticHeatMap,
1082  result->azimuthStaticHeatMapSize * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t));
1083 
1084  tlvIdx++;
1085  }
1086 
1087  /* Send data for range/Doppler heatmap */
1088  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeDopplerHeatMap == 1)
1089  {
1090  UART_writePolling (uartHandle,
1091  (uint8_t*)&tl[tlvIdx],
1092  sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl));
1093 
1094  UART_writePolling (uartHandle,
1095  (uint8_t*)detMatrix,
1096  tl[tlvIdx].length);

1527 static int32_t MmwDemo_eventCallbackFxn(uint16_t msgId, uint16_t sbId, uint16_t sbLen, uint8_t *payload)
1528 {
1529  uint16_t asyncSB = RL_GET_SBID_FROM_UNIQ_SBID(sbId);
1530 
1531  /* Process the received message: */
1532  switch (msgId)
1533  {
1534  case RL_RF_ASYNC_EVENT_MSG:
1535  {
1536  /* Received Asychronous Message: */
1537  switch (asyncSB)
1538  {
1539  case RL_RF_AE_CPUFAULT_SB:
1540  {
1541  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
1542  break;
1543  }
1544  case RL_RF_AE_ESMFAULT_SB:
1545  {
1546  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
1547  break;
1548  }
1549  case RL_RF_AE_ANALOG_FAULT_SB:
1550  {
1551  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
1552  break;
1553  }
1554  case RL_RF_AE_INITCALIBSTATUS_SB:
1555  {
1556  rlRfInitComplete_t* ptrRFInitCompleteMessage;
1557  uint32_t calibrationStatus;
1558 
1559  /* Get the RF-Init completion message: */
1560  ptrRFInitCompleteMessage = (rlRfInitComplete_t*)payload;
1561  calibrationStatus = ptrRFInitCompleteMessage->calibStatus & 0xFFFU;
1562 
1563  /* Display the calibration status: */
1564  CLI_write ("Debug: Init Calibration Status = 0x%x\n", calibrationStatus);
1565  break;
1566  }
1567  case RL_RF_AE_FRAME_TRIGGER_RDY_SB:
1568  {
1569  gMmwMssMCB.stats.frameTriggerReady++;
1570  break;
1571  }
1572  case RL_RF_AE_MON_TIMING_FAIL_REPORT_SB:
1573  {
1574  gMmwMssMCB.stats.failedTimingReports++;
1575  break;
1576  }
1577  case RL_RF_AE_RUN_TIME_CALIB_REPORT_SB:
1578  {
1579  gMmwMssMCB.stats.calibrationReports++;
1580  break;
1581  }
1582  case RL_RF_AE_FRAME_END_SB:
1583  {
1584  gMmwMssMCB.stats.sensorStopped++;
1585  DebugP_log0("App: BSS stop (frame end) received\n");
1586 
1587  MmwDemo_dataPathStop();
1588  break;
1589  }
1590  default:
1591  {
1592  System_printf ("Error: Asynchronous Event SB Id %d not handled\n", asyncSB);
1593  break;
1594  }
1595  }
1596  break;
1597  }
1598  default:
1599  {
1600  System_printf ("Error: Asynchronous message %d is NOT handled\n", msgId);
1601  break;
1602  }
1603  }
1604  return 0;
1605 }

1627 static void MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_reportFxn
1628 (
1629  DPM_Report reportType,
1630  uint32_t instanceId,
1631  int32_t errCode,
1632  uint32_t arg0,
1633  uint32_t arg1
1634 )
1635 {
1636  /* Only errors are logged on the console: */
1637  if ((errCode != 0) || (instanceId != DPC_OBJDET_INSTANCEID))
1638  {
1639  /* Error: Detected log on the console and die all errors are FATAL currently. */
1640  System_printf ("Error: DPM Report %d received with error:%d arg0:0x%x arg1:0x%x\n",
1641  reportType, errCode, arg0, arg1);
1642  DebugP_assert (0);
1643  }
1644 
1645  /* Processing further is based on the reports received: This is the control of the profile
1646  * state machine: */
1647  switch (reportType)
1648  {
1649  case DPM_Report_IOCTL:
1650  {
1651 
1652  /*****************************************************************
1653  * DPC has been configured without an error:
1654  * - This is an indication that the profile configuration commands
1655  * went through without any issues.
1656  *****************************************************************/
1657  DebugP_log1("App: DPM Report IOCTL, command = %d\n", arg0);
1658 
1659  if (arg0 == DPC_OBJDET_IOCTL__STATIC_PRE_START_CFG)
1660  {
1661  DPC_ObjectDetection_PreStartCfg *cfg;
1662  DPC_ObjectDetection_DPC_IOCTL_preStartCfg_memUsage *memUsage;
1663 
1664  cfg = (DPC_ObjectDetection_PreStartCfg*)arg1;
1665 
1666  memUsage = &cfg->memUsage;
1667 
1668  System_printf("============ Heap Memory Stats ============\n");
1669  System_printf("%20s %12s %12s %12s %12s\n", " ", "Size", "Used", "Free", "DPCUsed");
1670  System_printf("%20s %12d %12d %12d %12d\n", "System Heap(L2)",
1671  memUsage->SystemHeapTotal, memUsage->SystemHeapUsed,
1672  memUsage->SystemHeapTotal - memUsage->SystemHeapUsed,
1673  memUsage->SystemHeapDPCUsed);
1674 
1675  System_printf("%20s %12d %12d %12d\n", "L3",
1676  memUsage->L3RamTotal,
1677  memUsage->L3RamUsage,
1678  memUsage->L3RamTotal - memUsage->L3RamUsage);
1679 
1680  System_printf("%20s %12d %12d %12d\n", "localRam(L2)",
1681  memUsage->CoreLocalRamTotal,
1682  memUsage->CoreLocalRamUsage,
1683  memUsage->CoreLocalRamTotal - memUsage->CoreLocalRamUsage);
1684  }
1685 
1686  switch(arg0)
1687  {
1688  /* The following ioctls take longer time to finish. It causes DPM to queue IOCTL requests on DSS before
1689  * they are handled. However DPM has limited pipe queues, hence adding sync points in demo to avoid
1690  * sending too many such ioctls to DSS at a time.
1691  * The semaphore blocks CLI task to wait for the response from DSS before sending the next ioctl.
1692  */
1693  case DPC_OBJDET_IOCTL__STATIC_PRE_START_CFG:
1694  case DPC_OBJDET_IOCTL__STATIC_PRE_START_COMMON_CFG:
1695  Semaphore_post(gMmwMssMCB.DPMioctlSemHandle);
1696  break;
1697  default:
1698  break;
1699  }
1700  break;
1701  }
1702  case DPM_Report_DPC_STARTED:
1703  {
1704  /*****************************************************************
1705  * DPC has been started without an error:
1706  * - notify sensor management task that DPC is started.
1707  *****************************************************************/
1708  DebugP_log0("App: DPM Report DPC Started\n");
1709  Semaphore_post(gMmwMssMCB.DPMstartSemHandle);
1710  break;
1711  }
1712  case DPM_Report_NOTIFY_DPC_RESULT:
1713  {
1714  /*****************************************************************
1715  * datapath has finished frame processing, results are reported
1716  *****************************************************************/
1717  DPM_Buffer* ptrResult;
1718 
1719  /* Get the result: */
1720  ptrResult = (DPM_Buffer*)arg0;
1721 
1722  MmwDemo_handleObjectDetResult(ptrResult);
1723  break;
1724  }
1725  case DPM_Report_DPC_ASSERT:
1726  {
1727  DPM_DPCAssert* ptrAssert;
1728 
1729  /*****************************************************************
1730  * DPC Fault has been detected:
1731  * - This implies that the DPC has crashed.
1732  * - The argument0 points to the DPC assertion information
1733  *****************************************************************/
1734  ptrAssert = (DPM_DPCAssert*)arg0;
1735  CLI_write("Obj Det DPC Exception: %s, line %d.\n", ptrAssert->fileName,
1736  ptrAssert->lineNum);
1737  break;
1738  }
1739  case DPM_Report_DPC_STOPPED:
1740  {
1741  /*****************************************************************
1742  * DPC has been stopped without an error:
1743  * - This implies that the DPC can either be reconfigured or
1744  * restarted.
1745  *****************************************************************/
1746  DebugP_log0("App: DPM Report DPC Stopped\n");
1747  Semaphore_post(gMmwMssMCB.DPMstopSemHandle);
1748  break;
1749  }
1750  case DPM_Report_DPC_INFO:
1751  case DPM_Report_NOTIFY_DPC_RESULT_ACKED:
1752  {
1753  /* Currently objDetHwa does not use this feature. */
1754  break;
1755  }
1756  default:
1757  {
1758  DebugP_assert (0);
1759  break;
1760  }
1761  }
1762  return;
1763 }

2558  }

2560  /* Create binary semaphores which is used to signal DPM_start/DPM_stop/DPM_ioctl is done

2571  *****************************************************************************/

2575

2597  * between the domains. This is a prerequiste and always needs to be invoked. */
2598  if (MMWave_sync (gMmwMssMCB.ctrlHandle, &errCode) < 0)
2599  {
2600  /* Error: Unable to synchronize the mmWave control module */

2602  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
2603  return;
2604  }
2605  System_printf ("Debug: mmWave Control Synchronization was successful\n");
2606

2608  * Launch the mmWave control execution task
2609  * - This should have a higher priroity than any other task which uses the
2610  * mmWave control API
2611  *****************************************************************************/

2613  taskParams.priority = MMWDEMO_MMWAVE_CTRL_TASK_PRIORITY;
2614  taskParams.stackSize = 3*1024;
2615  gMmwMssMCB.taskHandles.mmwaveCtrl = Task_create(MmwDemo_mmWaveCtrlTask, &taskParams, NULL);
2616

2618  * Initialization of the DPM Module:
2619  *****************************************************************************/

2621

2624  dpmInitCfg.ptrProcChainCfg = NULL;
2625  dpmInitCfg.instanceId = DPC_OBJDET_INSTANCEID;
2626  dpmInitCfg.domain = DPM_Domain_REMOTE;
2627  dpmInitCfg.reportFxn = MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_reportFxn;

2634  {

2636  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
2637  return;
2638  }
2639 
2640  /* Synchronization: This will synchronize the execution of the datapath module
2641  * between the domains. This is a prerequiste and always needs to be invoked. */
2642  while (1)
2643  {
2644  int32_t syncStatus;
2645 
2646  /* Get the synchronization status: */
2647  syncStatus = DPM_synch (gMmwMssMCB.objDetDpmHandle, &errCode);
2648  if (syncStatus < 0)
2649  {
2650  /* Error: Unable to synchronize the framework */
2651  System_printf ("Error: DPM Synchronization failed [Error code %d]\n", errCode);
2652  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
2653  return;
2654  }
2655  if (syncStatus == 1)
2656  {
2657  /* Synchronization acheived: */
2658  break;
2659  }
2660  /* Sleep and poll again: */
2661  Task_sleep(1);
2662  }
2663

2665  Task_Params_init(&taskParams);
2666  taskParams.priority = MMWDEMO_DPC_OBJDET_DPM_TASK_PRIORITY;
2667  taskParams.stackSize = 4*1024;

2677  *****************************************************************************/
